00:23.899 --> 00:25.984
[INSECTS BUZZING]

00:26.109 --> 00:29.113
[RAIN FALLING]

00:33.033 --> 00:35.252
[THUNDER RUMBLING]

00:35.994 --> 00:37.462
[CAR DOOR CLOSES]

00:38.830 --> 00:41.083
[TRUNK OPENS]

00:53.220 --> 00:55.689
[BIRDS CHIRPING]

01:11.488 --> 01:14.537
[SAWING NOISES]

01:19.454 --> 01:22.458
[SHOVELING DIRT]

01:36.263 --> 01:40.234
DANGER, DON'T PICK UP HITCHHIKERS

01:45.230 --> 01:47.574
[CAR APPROACHING]

01:55.324 --> 01:57.577
Brilliant.

02:11.089 --> 02:12.841
[CAR HORN HONKS]

02:27.981 --> 02:29.650
[MUSIC PLAYING ON THE RADIO]

02:29.775 --> 02:31.698
Should we stop?

02:32.819 --> 02:34.655
Absolutely not.

02:34.780 --> 02:36.703
We don't pick up hitchhikers.

02:37.574 --> 02:39.827
You can't be serious. It's too dangerous.

02:49.920 --> 02:51.263
[BIRDS CHIRPING]

02:53.840 --> 02:56.309
Come on. Come on!

03:01.431 --> 03:03.650
[BIRDS CHIRPING]

03:28.375 --> 03:31.629
[CAR APPROACHING]

03:39.761 --> 03:41.638
Calm down, or I'll make you calm down.

03:41.763 --> 03:42.973
Hey.

03:43.098 --> 03:44.516
- Get out of the car.
- No!

03:44.641 --> 03:47.269
Are you all right? Hey! Hey!

03:47.477 --> 03:51.027
- I said, get out!
- Hey, hey, hey, hey!

03:52.899 --> 03:54.401
[GRUNTS]

03:55.861 --> 03:57.446
What the hell do you think you're doing?

03:57.571 --> 04:00.657
You want this guy? You're trying
to pull a fast one on me?

04:00.782 --> 04:03.160
I took you everywhere!
I was at your beck and call!

04:03.285 --> 04:06.830
Get out of here! Just go!
You can keep that whore!

04:07.622 --> 04:08.544
[CAR DOOR OPENING]

04:10.751 --> 04:12.836
Asshole! Dickhead!

04:12.961 --> 04:14.755
[ENGINE STARTING]

04:14.880 --> 04:19.009
- You're just a slut!
- Get out of here!

04:19.134 --> 04:21.101
What a nightmare, this guy.
I can't believe this.

04:21.261 --> 04:22.729
[SIGHS]

04:23.638 --> 04:25.349
Thank you.

04:25.474 --> 04:27.442
This could have been really bad.

04:28.685 --> 04:32.648
- What are you doing here?
- I'm sorry, I don't speak French.

04:32.773 --> 04:35.025
Are you English?

04:35.150 --> 04:36.318
- Yeah.
- [SIGHS]

04:36.443 --> 04:39.287
- You speak English?
- But of course.

04:40.071 --> 04:41.664
[SIGHS]

04:49.414 --> 04:51.291
[FLICKING LIGHTER]

04:51.708 --> 04:53.130
[BIRDS CHIRPING]

04:55.128 --> 04:56.713
[EXHALES CIGARETTE]

04:56.838 --> 04:58.340
Oh. Are you all right?

04:58.465 --> 05:01.927
It's nothing. I am an idiot.

05:02.052 --> 05:03.303
What about you?

05:03.428 --> 05:05.764
Oh, just a little accident.

05:05.889 --> 05:07.106
[LAUGHS]

05:08.767 --> 05:11.019
So, do you know that guy?

05:11.144 --> 05:13.238
No, I was hitchhiking, and he picked me up.

05:13.438 --> 05:16.358
I don't know how you say it in English. Stop.

05:16.483 --> 05:19.569
- How do you...? Stop. You understand?
- Yeah. No.

05:19.694 --> 05:21.492
[LAUGHS]

05:22.531 --> 05:25.826
- My name is Véronique.
- Jack.

05:27.327 --> 05:30.706
- Where do you go, Jack?
- I'm just trying to get home.

05:30.831 --> 05:33.250
- To England?
- Hmm.

05:33.375 --> 05:35.877
I've been down south, just hanging out.

05:36.002 --> 05:38.255
I thought it was time to get back.

05:38.380 --> 05:42.467
The journey should've taken me a couple
of days, but the lifts just dried up.

05:42.592 --> 05:46.012
Feels like I've walked halfway across France.

05:46.137 --> 05:48.432
I know what that's like.

05:48.557 --> 05:51.059
Life on the road.

05:51.184 --> 05:53.687
What about you? You've been traveling long?

05:53.812 --> 05:55.313
I'm always traveling.

05:55.438 --> 05:57.357
It's good for the soul, you know?

05:57.482 --> 05:58.900
- Got to keep moving.
- [LAUGHS]

05:59.025 --> 06:01.820
Yeah. I'm a bit of a restless soul myself.

06:01.945 --> 06:04.164
[BIRDS CHIRPING]

06:04.322 --> 06:05.619
Where you headed?

06:06.741 --> 06:08.910
Wherever I can get to.

06:09.035 --> 06:10.582
You don't have a home?

06:10.829 --> 06:13.548
No. Not anymore.

06:21.673 --> 06:24.552
- [LAUGHING]
- [GROANING]

06:25.594 --> 06:28.188
I'm sorry.

06:29.347 --> 06:31.892
One, two, three...

06:32.017 --> 06:33.310
Scissors!

06:33.435 --> 06:35.353
- I win!
- Again.

06:35.478 --> 06:37.446
What the fuck?

06:39.691 --> 06:42.194
Come on! What is wrong with these people?

06:42.360 --> 06:43.820
[SIGHS]

06:43.945 --> 06:45.989
No, seriously, what the fuck?

06:46.114 --> 06:48.208
I think it's because of the road killer.

06:48.366 --> 06:50.660
I think it's because
of the killer of the road.

06:50.785 --> 06:52.412
How do you translate?

06:52.537 --> 06:53.663
Road killer?

06:53.788 --> 06:56.708
- Yeah, you've heard of him?
- No.

06:56.833 --> 06:58.251
- [SIGHS]
- He's famous, though.

06:58.376 --> 07:02.256
He's a serious killer,
like, um, Jack the Ripper.

07:02.422 --> 07:04.090
You mean a serial killer.

07:04.215 --> 07:05.967
Yeah, well, that's what I said.

07:06.092 --> 07:08.891
They found corpses on the road,
their throat slit.

07:09.095 --> 07:12.224
Like, really bad things
have been happening lately.

07:12.390 --> 07:13.558
People are scared...

07:13.683 --> 07:15.894
The whole area is terrified.

07:16.019 --> 07:18.480
Like dead people on the road,
do you understand?

07:18.605 --> 07:19.898
You're not scared?

07:20.023 --> 07:22.067
Of course I am.
That's why I don't want to stay here.

07:22.192 --> 07:24.286
Well, you know...

07:24.444 --> 07:26.863
IN FRENCH: We need to help each other.

07:26.988 --> 07:29.491
Ah? You speak French now?

07:29.616 --> 07:31.201
A little.

07:31.326 --> 07:33.044
I see.

07:35.163 --> 07:38.917
I agree, it's better
if we stick together. It's safer.

07:39.042 --> 07:42.003
Safety in numbers, yes?

07:42.128 --> 07:44.005
[CAR APPROACHING]

07:45.215 --> 07:46.716
One, two, three...

07:46.841 --> 07:49.515
- Paper!
- Are you serious?

07:51.680 --> 07:53.432
[CAR CLOSELY APPROACHING]

07:56.935 --> 07:59.029
And why would you stop?

07:59.813 --> 08:01.531
[SIGHS]

08:02.691 --> 08:04.034
[CRICKETS CHIRPING]

08:05.527 --> 08:07.029
[SIGHS]

08:08.363 --> 08:09.906
IN FRENCH: Do you want some...

08:10.031 --> 08:12.242
- Chair?
- [CHUCKLES]

08:12.367 --> 08:14.202
Yeah. Thanks.

08:14.327 --> 08:15.203
[SIGHS]

08:15.328 --> 08:17.455
IN FRENCH: Do you want a chair?

08:17.580 --> 08:20.000
At least, I hope this is what you mean...

08:20.125 --> 08:22.173
[FIRE CRACKLING]

08:31.469 --> 08:33.062
[RIPPING OUT A PAGE]

08:36.099 --> 08:40.145
Ah. "Do you want a chair?"

08:40.270 --> 08:42.443
Yeah. Good.

08:44.190 --> 08:45.612
I was practicing.

08:46.192 --> 08:47.910
My signature.

08:49.487 --> 08:52.491
What about you? Why don't you learn French?

09:02.167 --> 09:04.261
[FIRE CRACKLING]

09:13.136 --> 09:14.558
Why don't you carry a bag?

09:17.432 --> 09:19.651
It's a bit weird that...

09:21.061 --> 09:22.687
To travel without bags?

09:22.812 --> 09:24.105
Well, I lost them.

09:24.230 --> 09:26.316
Lost them?

09:26.441 --> 09:29.027
- Actually, they were stolen...
- Oh.

09:29.152 --> 09:31.325
In the train station in Nice.

09:32.405 --> 09:34.157
Worst day ever.

09:34.282 --> 09:38.332
Lost everything except my... passport.

09:40.121 --> 09:41.289
Oh, come on.

09:41.414 --> 09:42.832
- Wait!
- Give it back.

09:42.957 --> 09:44.675
I'm just looking.

09:46.127 --> 09:48.797
Jack Withe. Born on August 12.

09:48.922 --> 09:51.596
They don't like you smiling in those things.

09:51.758 --> 09:54.052
I mean, what's wrong with a little smile?

09:54.177 --> 09:56.020
They need to lighten up.

09:57.013 --> 09:58.264
I look proper.

09:58.389 --> 09:59.933
No. You look cute.

10:00.058 --> 10:01.685
[SIGHS]

10:02.769 --> 10:05.522
We were born a week apart.

10:05.647 --> 10:06.982
I'm older.

10:07.107 --> 10:09.576
- Cool.
- Yeah, it's cool.

10:13.905 --> 10:15.657
You're not afraid of me?

10:15.782 --> 10:17.375
No.

10:18.827 --> 10:21.204
You're a good guy.

10:21.329 --> 10:22.956
I can feel it.

10:24.124 --> 10:25.709
How do you know I'm not a killer?

10:25.834 --> 10:27.461
[SNICKERS]

10:36.219 --> 10:38.017
[FIRE CRACKLING]

10:40.932 --> 10:42.980
[BIRDS CHIRPING]

10:52.443 --> 10:54.571
[BIRDS CHIRPING]

11:06.166 --> 11:08.168
[SPLASHING]

11:12.380 --> 11:15.967
Come on in! The water is so nice! Come on!

11:16.092 --> 11:17.389
It's great.

11:18.887 --> 11:21.310
[PANTING]

11:22.682 --> 11:25.401
Wondered where you'd got to.
Thought you just left.

11:25.935 --> 11:28.605
Not yet. I'm not going anywhere.

11:28.730 --> 11:29.898
Cool.

11:30.023 --> 11:31.608
I mean...

11:31.733 --> 11:33.531
It's fine. Good.

11:33.693 --> 11:35.286
[CHUCKLING]

11:38.281 --> 11:42.952
Uh, you know how I told you
that I lost my, um...

11:43.077 --> 11:45.121
Yeah?

11:45.246 --> 11:46.372
My girl...

11:46.497 --> 11:48.750
Ex-girlfriend...

11:51.502 --> 11:53.671
- Never mind.
- No, tell me.

11:53.796 --> 11:56.174
What did she do? Did she steal your bags?

11:56.299 --> 11:59.177
She just dumped me for my best friend.

11:59.302 --> 12:01.387
That's not exactly a best friend.

12:01.512 --> 12:03.181
We had this big plan...

12:03.306 --> 12:06.893
to meet in Nice and travel all across Europe.

12:07.018 --> 12:10.897
Instead, I walked in on their...
sweaty, naked bodies.

12:11.022 --> 12:12.440
It was complicated.

12:12.565 --> 12:14.651
Shit.

12:14.776 --> 12:15.860
Bad luck.

12:15.985 --> 12:18.279
Like I said, worst day ever.

12:18.404 --> 12:19.872
I can imagine.

12:20.865 --> 12:23.914
I don't give a shit about that anymore.

12:25.787 --> 12:27.505
You should forget about her.

12:28.623 --> 12:31.593
Or she will stick to you like a bad odor.

12:32.418 --> 12:34.003
Live in the present.

12:34.128 --> 12:36.096
Do what you want.

12:36.839 --> 12:38.716
You are free.

12:40.009 --> 12:41.727
[SNICKERS]

12:43.471 --> 12:45.565
You're a nice kisser.

12:45.723 --> 12:47.350
Do you understand?

12:53.815 --> 12:55.442
[SNICKERS]

13:10.164 --> 13:12.792
[BIRDS CHIRPING]

13:15.003 --> 13:16.755
[CAR APPROACHING]

13:27.015 --> 13:28.733
Come on!

13:29.267 --> 13:31.477
Come on, let's go! British reg.

13:31.602 --> 13:32.854
[ENGINE STOPS]

13:36.107 --> 13:38.989
- Please tell me you're going to England.
- I am sorry.

13:39.193 --> 13:41.988
I can take you as far as I can,
but not so far.

13:42.113 --> 13:46.326
Oh. I just thought
with the registration plate...

13:46.451 --> 13:50.663
The car? It's the car of my wife.
She's English.

13:50.788 --> 13:52.506
But do come in!

13:53.624 --> 13:55.835
Véronique! You coming or what?

13:55.960 --> 13:57.212
Your girlfriend?

13:57.337 --> 13:58.880
Could you just give me one minute?

13:59.005 --> 14:00.757
Huh.

14:01.966 --> 14:03.551
Véronique...

14:03.676 --> 14:07.055
Let's go. Safety in numbers, remember?

14:07.180 --> 14:08.473
Okay.

14:08.598 --> 14:10.600
[BIRDS CHIRPING]

14:17.899 --> 14:19.400
You travel light.

14:19.525 --> 14:22.369
All the way to England with nothing?

14:23.321 --> 14:25.865
- Long story.
- Well, then, you have to tell me the story.

14:25.990 --> 14:28.201
I am interested. Where did it start,
how does it end...?

14:28.326 --> 14:31.250
- [ENGINE STARTING]
- Et cetera, et cetera.

14:40.838 --> 14:42.090
[FRENCH MUSIC PLAYING ON RADIO]

14:42.215 --> 14:43.800
# I am dying #

14:43.925 --> 14:45.677
# I am clocking in #

14:45.843 --> 14:47.686
# Near my house #

14:47.845 --> 14:49.222
# In my heart #

14:49.389 --> 14:50.515
[TURNS OFF RADIO]

14:50.640 --> 14:53.644
Well, excuse me. Make yourself at home.

14:53.851 --> 14:55.186
[LAUGHING]

14:55.311 --> 14:57.154
I thought it was a bit quiet.

14:59.315 --> 15:02.410
What I really like is to listen
to the sound of this car.

15:02.568 --> 15:06.573
You know? This engine sounds beautiful.

15:16.332 --> 15:17.709
[SMALL IMPACT, TIRES SCREECHING]

15:17.875 --> 15:19.669
What the...?

15:19.794 --> 15:22.047
- What was that?
- My God.

15:23.089 --> 15:25.638
Stay in the car. I'll go see what it is.

15:31.681 --> 15:33.266
What'd he say?

15:33.391 --> 15:36.065
He said, "Stay in the car."

15:41.816 --> 15:43.693
[LAUGHING]

15:46.571 --> 15:49.745
Sorry, I laugh from the nerves.

15:49.907 --> 15:51.451
It's a rabbit.

15:51.576 --> 15:52.702
[LAUGHS]

15:55.830 --> 15:58.708
It's crazy how many animals die on the road.

15:58.833 --> 16:00.293
Poor thing.

16:00.418 --> 16:02.261
Yeah, well...

16:04.088 --> 16:05.673
Ah.

16:05.798 --> 16:08.392
As long as we're not stuck in a ditch.

16:09.218 --> 16:13.273
I've known dumb ones, but as far as
rabbits go, this one takes the cake.

16:14.015 --> 16:16.359
Mistakes happen.

16:29.947 --> 16:30.948
[SIGHS]

16:31.073 --> 16:32.241
We should bury it.

16:32.366 --> 16:33.576
[LAUGHS]

16:33.701 --> 16:36.245
You must be joking. I'll deal with it.

16:36.370 --> 16:38.039
You must be hungry.

16:38.164 --> 16:41.338
So we're going to eat some rabbit.

16:43.002 --> 16:44.337
Ah.

16:44.462 --> 16:46.297
I haven't been to England for a long time.

16:46.422 --> 16:47.965
It must have changed a lot.

16:48.090 --> 16:50.343
What about you, miss?
Which way are you going?

16:50.468 --> 16:52.512
Why?

16:52.637 --> 16:54.305
I was just wondering.

16:54.430 --> 16:58.017
I was just wondering
if you were going the same way.

16:58.142 --> 17:00.061
Both of you.

17:00.186 --> 17:01.354
It's plausible.

17:01.479 --> 17:03.777
It's none of your business.

17:05.358 --> 17:06.692
I don't know.

17:06.817 --> 17:08.944
I have nowhere to go.

17:10.863 --> 17:12.490
Fair enough.

17:12.615 --> 17:14.333
[ENGINE STARTING]

17:25.211 --> 17:26.884
Tired, right?

17:27.922 --> 17:30.516
Well, it's getting late.

17:32.009 --> 17:34.303
Weather may change.

17:34.428 --> 17:38.353
It's not safe on the road in the night.

17:39.809 --> 17:43.312
You can stay the night with me.

17:43.437 --> 17:46.732
My wife likes to have English company.

17:46.857 --> 17:51.154
That's very kind,
but I've really got to get back.

17:51.279 --> 17:54.240
I'm supposed to be visiting
my parents. They'll be worried.

17:54.365 --> 17:58.836
I understand. Parents worry.
That's what they do.

18:01.080 --> 18:03.378
What about you, miss? Your parents?

18:03.541 --> 18:05.714
Dead. Both of them.

18:06.752 --> 18:09.005
- They're dead.
- Véronique, I'm so sorry.

18:09.130 --> 18:11.507
Don't be sorry. It was a long time ago.

18:11.632 --> 18:13.430
A long time.

18:15.177 --> 18:17.597
That is very sad.

18:17.722 --> 18:19.599
Parents...

18:20.391 --> 18:22.359
They are important.

18:24.562 --> 18:27.907
Well, uh, Jack, here is my suggestion.

18:28.065 --> 18:29.108
You come to my home,

18:29.233 --> 18:32.278
my wife will make, uh, good, uh, food.

18:32.403 --> 18:35.490
You eat, you sleep, and tomorrow...

18:35.615 --> 18:38.493
Tomorrow, I will take you
where you need to go.

18:38.618 --> 18:40.369
To Calais for the ferries.

18:40.494 --> 18:42.705
You'll be home in the afternoon.

18:42.830 --> 18:45.424
Sounds too good to be true.

18:46.542 --> 18:48.628
- But you know what...
- Oh, wait! I am such an idiot!

18:48.753 --> 18:51.589
I forget completely,
there is strike in Calais!

18:51.714 --> 18:53.633
- A strike?
- Mm-hmm.

18:53.758 --> 18:55.134
No ferries.

18:55.259 --> 18:56.932
Oh, I didn't know.

18:57.094 --> 18:58.971
We'll figure something out.

18:59.138 --> 19:00.981
Oh, yeah? And what is that?

19:01.140 --> 19:04.143
You're going to swim across the Channel?

19:04.268 --> 19:06.896
No, maybe better to come to my home.

19:07.021 --> 19:10.483
And I will make you some nice, hot coffee.

19:10.608 --> 19:13.069
Actually, I could kill for a cup of tea.

19:13.194 --> 19:14.695
Tea?

19:14.820 --> 19:17.289
How very... English.

19:56.237 --> 19:57.033
[PULLS PARKING BRAKE]

19:57.196 --> 19:58.698
Ah! Damn it.

19:58.823 --> 20:00.871
I've looked everywhere for it.

20:02.576 --> 20:04.795
Why did I put it here?

20:06.163 --> 20:09.041
Jack, this is a bad idea.

20:09.166 --> 20:11.335
Let's just get some food and clean up.

20:11.460 --> 20:13.254
We can leave after dinner, yeah?

20:13.379 --> 20:14.922
I completely forgot where I put it.

20:15.047 --> 20:16.924
Here. Please.

20:17.049 --> 20:18.722
Thank you.

20:20.302 --> 20:23.723
My wife will be very happy to see you.

20:23.848 --> 20:25.475
[BIRDS CHIRPING]

20:28.811 --> 20:31.897
Here we are, my house.

20:32.022 --> 20:33.820
[CAR HORN]

20:42.366 --> 20:46.454
Mary, darling, look who I've brought home.
Two young travelers lost on the road.

20:46.579 --> 20:49.206
Our friend here is a young Englishman, Jack,

20:49.331 --> 20:53.837
and his friend is a poor... orphan
with nowhere to go.

20:56.213 --> 20:57.840
Come in.

20:58.716 --> 21:00.514
[BIRDS CHIRPING]

21:04.388 --> 21:05.514
[DOOR CLOSING]

21:07.933 --> 21:10.982
Darling, would you show Jack his room?

21:12.271 --> 21:14.607
Of course. Follow me.

21:14.732 --> 21:16.700
And I'll show you yours.

21:16.859 --> 21:19.032
I can carry that.

21:24.033 --> 21:26.252
Monsieur said you were English.

21:30.998 --> 21:33.834
Have you lived in France long?

21:33.959 --> 21:35.381
Too long.

21:38.172 --> 21:42.969
I lived in England for a while,
before I ended up here.

21:44.261 --> 21:46.514
But I am originally from the States.

21:46.639 --> 21:49.483
My husband seems to forget.

21:50.935 --> 21:54.563
Oh. It hasn't been used in a while.

21:54.688 --> 21:56.065
Your visit is...

21:59.777 --> 22:00.824
unexpected.

22:01.987 --> 22:03.830
Good God.

22:05.449 --> 22:07.702
I didn't have time
to clean the room properly.

22:08.828 --> 22:12.924
Well, why would I?
I mean, you've only just arrived.

22:15.417 --> 22:17.378
Anyway...

22:17.503 --> 22:20.131
I hope you'll at least be comfortable.

22:20.297 --> 22:24.097
Oh, believe me,
anything beats sleeping rough.

22:24.844 --> 22:28.599
Oh, but you mustn't do that.

22:29.723 --> 22:31.145
It's very dangerous.

22:31.308 --> 22:33.978
Yeah, so everyone keeps telling me.

22:34.103 --> 22:37.107
But it's not every day you meet
someone as kind as you, Madame.

22:39.358 --> 22:41.485
You can call me Mary.

22:41.610 --> 22:43.988
Well, thank you, Mary.

22:48.075 --> 22:49.873
[SIGHS]

22:57.543 --> 22:59.386
Is everything all right?

23:01.547 --> 23:04.096
I don't know why I did that, um...

23:06.218 --> 23:08.312
Unexpected.

23:10.347 --> 23:12.016
That's the word I was looking for.

23:12.141 --> 23:13.768
[SIGHS]

23:23.777 --> 23:25.613
Please...

23:25.738 --> 23:27.206
Have a rest and freshen up.

23:27.364 --> 23:30.163
I'll see if I can...
find you some clean clothes.

23:34.997 --> 23:37.341
We can have a chat later.

23:51.931 --> 23:53.478
[SIGHS]

23:53.974 --> 23:56.102
[BIRDS CHIRPING]

24:02.107 --> 24:04.075
[THUNDER RUMBLING]

24:05.653 --> 24:07.030
[BIRDS CHIRPING]

24:14.745 --> 24:16.213
[LOUD BANGING NOISE]

25:27.317 --> 25:28.660
[SIGHS]

25:39.204 --> 25:40.376
[DOOR UNLOCKING]

25:41.832 --> 25:44.168
What do you think of this place?

25:44.293 --> 25:46.462
It's cozy.

25:46.587 --> 25:48.631
- Cozy?
- Yeah.

25:48.756 --> 25:49.882
What's your room like?

25:50.007 --> 25:52.176
Who cares? Let's get out of this place.

25:52.301 --> 25:54.887
- I really don't like these people.
- No. They're all right.

25:55.012 --> 25:57.356
I think they're just lonely.

25:58.348 --> 25:59.850
[SIGHS]

26:11.070 --> 26:12.743
[SIGHS]

26:19.161 --> 26:21.497
Did you see how they were looking at me?

26:21.622 --> 26:22.669
They're weird.

26:23.707 --> 26:25.793
I don't trust them.

26:25.918 --> 26:27.628
They didn't even give us the same room.

26:27.753 --> 26:30.965
I think they're just a bit old-fashioned.

26:31.090 --> 26:34.134
And why do you want to stay
in the same room as me anyway?

26:34.259 --> 26:36.762
I told you, I'm dangerous.

26:38.472 --> 26:40.395
Youngsters, dinner is ready.

26:40.557 --> 26:43.602
Oh, I'm just finishing up here.

26:43.727 --> 26:46.105
As soon as you'll be ready.

26:48.732 --> 26:50.234
[SNICKERS]

26:51.360 --> 26:53.829
Old-fashioned?

26:54.488 --> 26:58.117
To your good health! As we say in French.

26:58.242 --> 27:01.291
- My love.
- Bon appetit.

27:03.330 --> 27:06.542
You know, my wife is an excellent, uh...

27:06.667 --> 27:09.753
What's the word in English to say...

27:09.878 --> 27:13.090
I'm afraid my English is... rusting.

27:13.215 --> 27:15.342
- Uh...
- Cook.

27:15.467 --> 27:16.677
Of course! Cook.

27:16.802 --> 27:18.595
[LAUGHING]

27:18.720 --> 27:21.473
It hits the nail right on the nose.

27:21.640 --> 27:24.143
You mean, on the head.

27:24.268 --> 27:28.364
You say tomato, I say open-heart surgery.

27:29.439 --> 27:31.487
[CHUCKLING]

27:38.198 --> 27:39.791
Is something wrong?

27:40.450 --> 27:42.703
I don't usually eat meat.

27:42.828 --> 27:45.330
- Though it does look very good!
- Oh!

27:45.455 --> 27:48.375
- I'm sorry. I didn't know.
- Oh. Why didn't you say?

27:48.500 --> 27:50.377
I'm sorry, I didn't mean to be rude.

27:50.502 --> 27:51.628
I'll take it off.

27:51.753 --> 27:52.921
Are you vegetarian?

27:53.046 --> 27:54.673
Yes. Oui.

27:54.798 --> 27:56.675
Oh...

27:56.800 --> 27:58.594
Um, we have some salad.

27:58.719 --> 28:00.804
No, it's fine, honestly. No.

28:00.929 --> 28:02.973
- Are you sure?
- No.

28:03.098 --> 28:05.934
You don't know what you miss, young man.

28:06.059 --> 28:07.811
In life, meat is...

28:07.936 --> 28:10.731
one of the most important... pleasure.

28:10.856 --> 28:13.609
Not only pleasure, but, you know.

28:17.571 --> 28:19.823
We say in France, you know...

28:19.948 --> 28:21.408
It melts in your mouth.

28:21.533 --> 28:25.704
Like truffle, chocolate. Chocolate truffle.

28:25.829 --> 28:28.707
You should try. Try it.

28:28.832 --> 28:33.754
Anyway, how can you imagine
such a handsome boy...

28:33.879 --> 28:35.964
being a homme-lette?

28:36.089 --> 28:37.841
[CHUCKLING]

28:41.511 --> 28:44.681
Don't mind him, he's just... teasing.

28:44.806 --> 28:46.266
Well, no, no, I am not.

28:46.391 --> 28:48.359
What is wrong with you?

28:50.103 --> 28:53.023
I would rather be a vegetarian

28:53.148 --> 28:56.402
than stuff my face
with all the flesh that you eat.

28:57.903 --> 28:59.871
Leave him be.

29:01.990 --> 29:03.913
She speaks.

29:05.702 --> 29:07.295
Merci.

29:11.708 --> 29:14.712
Oh, my God, what are you doing?

29:16.797 --> 29:18.925
I'm sorry.

29:23.637 --> 29:24.934
What's happening?

29:29.017 --> 29:31.987
Is there any problem? Or what?

29:33.188 --> 29:34.314
- No.
- So, I'm sorry.

29:34.439 --> 29:38.364
I'm sorry, okay? That's it.

29:41.446 --> 29:45.242
I really appreciate you
taking us both in like this.

29:45.367 --> 29:49.204
I mean, it feels like we've been hitching
forever with this road killer business.

29:49.329 --> 29:50.747
What did they call him?

29:50.872 --> 29:54.168
"Le tueur de la route."

29:54.293 --> 29:58.046
You've... you've heard of this killer?

29:58.171 --> 30:00.883
Well, he's famous. He's a serious killer.

30:01.008 --> 30:02.510
Serial killer.

30:02.759 --> 30:04.219
I don't...

30:04.344 --> 30:07.806
I don't want us to talk about it, okay?

30:07.931 --> 30:10.893
It upsets my wife, you know.

30:11.018 --> 30:15.063
They found a body close to here
in the last weeks.

30:15.188 --> 30:16.231
Young man.

30:16.356 --> 30:17.983
Would be the same age as you.

30:18.108 --> 30:20.657
I would rather talk about something else.

30:20.902 --> 30:22.738
Okay.

30:22.863 --> 30:26.074
I just wondered, you know.
It's kind of freaky.

30:26.199 --> 30:30.204
He'd been cut up and buried
in several pieces.

30:30.329 --> 30:32.915
- I'm sorry, darling! Oh!
- [GLASS BREAKING]

30:33.040 --> 30:34.416
Please.

30:34.541 --> 30:36.919
[PANTING]

30:42.799 --> 30:43.891
[DOOR CLOSING]

30:46.845 --> 30:50.015
- God, I am so sorry.
- Oh! It's not your fault.

30:50.140 --> 30:52.476
It's not your problem, no.

30:52.601 --> 30:54.899
Everybody's upset.

30:55.687 --> 30:59.524
People have lost their loved ones...

30:59.649 --> 31:01.902
in many ways.

31:02.527 --> 31:04.404
What... what do they know about the killer?

31:04.529 --> 31:06.615
Are there any leads?

31:06.740 --> 31:08.788
- Nothing.
- Nonsense!

31:10.327 --> 31:12.287
That's not true.

31:12.412 --> 31:14.831
Everybody knows around here
that he's lurking,

31:14.956 --> 31:17.334
looking for his next victim.

31:18.960 --> 31:21.429
- I'm sorry, but everybody knows.
- Yes, that's true.

31:24.549 --> 31:27.302
He only attacks the weak and the vulnerable.

31:27.427 --> 31:30.306
Children, old people.

31:31.181 --> 31:33.058
Women who travel alone.

31:33.183 --> 31:34.226
And hitchhikers.

31:34.351 --> 31:35.898
[LAUGHS]

31:37.854 --> 31:41.734
But anyway, you're safe here, you know.

31:41.900 --> 31:45.746
Really, Jack, don't worry.

31:46.655 --> 31:49.454
I'm sorry, I must assist my wife.

31:57.249 --> 31:58.717
[SIGHS]

31:58.875 --> 32:01.628
What the hell did you just say to him?

32:05.298 --> 32:07.016
You're a pain.

32:09.719 --> 32:10.766
[VÉRONIQUE SIGHS]

32:10.929 --> 32:12.727
[DOOR OPENING]

32:14.015 --> 32:15.517
[DOOR CLOSING]

32:20.522 --> 32:22.024
[SIGHS]

32:28.905 --> 32:30.657
[WIND RUSTLING]

32:33.201 --> 32:34.794
[CRICKETS CHIRPING]

32:35.912 --> 32:37.334
[ANIMAL CALL]

32:42.210 --> 32:43.803
[SIGHS]

32:50.677 --> 32:52.179
[SIGHS]

33:03.523 --> 33:05.275
[EXHALES]

33:12.115 --> 33:13.742
You want one?

33:22.834 --> 33:25.045
- Look, I'm sorry, okay?
- Will you stop saying you're sorry?

33:25.170 --> 33:29.511
You English spend your time apologizing.
Why do you always apologize?

33:30.425 --> 33:33.136
- I don't want to argue with you.
- It's fine. Forget it.

33:33.261 --> 33:35.309
[CRICKETS CHIRPING]

33:39.017 --> 33:41.816
How did you get that scar on your back?

33:41.978 --> 33:44.272
I saw it in the shower.

33:44.397 --> 33:47.401
Oh, my stepdad.

33:47.526 --> 33:49.528
Mom's boyfriend, whatever.

33:49.653 --> 33:52.614
We got into an argument when I was 12.

33:52.739 --> 33:55.951
We were on a road trip in France, actually.

33:56.076 --> 33:59.621
He lost it and hit me with a metal bar.

33:59.746 --> 34:02.958
- Got 10 stitches.
- Shit.

34:03.083 --> 34:05.544
I hit him back, in the face.

34:05.669 --> 34:08.047
He didn't bother me again after that.

34:12.509 --> 34:15.433
Never actually told anyone about that before.

34:18.639 --> 34:21.438
Well, my father never hit me, but...

34:23.353 --> 34:26.402
I don't know. I never fought back.

34:27.774 --> 34:30.243
How did they, you know...?

34:31.945 --> 34:34.447
- Sorry.
- No, no, it's okay.

34:34.572 --> 34:36.699
They say it's good to talk about it.

34:36.824 --> 34:38.873
[CRICKETS CHIRPING]

34:43.290 --> 34:44.882
Well...

34:47.335 --> 34:50.213
When I was little, my brother and I

34:50.338 --> 34:52.716
would play hide-and-seek in the fields.

34:52.841 --> 34:54.639
And...

34:56.428 --> 34:58.351
One day...

34:59.264 --> 35:01.562
We went a little too far.

35:03.768 --> 35:05.061
And...

35:05.186 --> 35:07.689
A tractor drove by.

35:10.483 --> 35:12.110
And...

35:14.529 --> 35:16.497
It was too late.

35:18.992 --> 35:20.785
The tractor...

35:20.910 --> 35:23.254
mauled my brother.

35:24.039 --> 35:27.417
So, now, whenever I think about my brother,

35:27.542 --> 35:29.385
I see blood.

35:30.587 --> 35:32.589
And...

35:32.714 --> 35:35.308
My mother always thought it was my fault.

35:38.595 --> 35:40.347
Do you understand?

35:40.472 --> 35:42.975
- Do you understand?
- Yeah.

35:43.141 --> 35:45.769
You have a brother, right?

35:45.894 --> 35:48.063
"Frère."

35:48.188 --> 35:51.775
It's silly, but I've never been to England.

35:51.900 --> 35:54.653
- Why don't you come with me, then?
- Really?

35:54.778 --> 35:56.321
Yeah.

35:56.446 --> 35:59.416
It's not just an empty suggestion?

36:00.200 --> 36:02.619
No, it's not an empty gesture.

36:02.744 --> 36:04.997
Seriously, come with me.

36:05.830 --> 36:08.500
But just for the record,
I really like France.

36:08.625 --> 36:10.673
[THUNDER RUMBLING]

36:25.475 --> 36:27.602
I wanted to do that since I first saw you.

36:27.727 --> 36:30.355
- Liar.
- Really.

36:30.480 --> 36:33.608
What, when you saw me in the car
with that weirdo?

36:33.733 --> 36:36.444
Well, maybe it was just a minute after that.

36:36.569 --> 36:40.244
- See?
- I'm not lying.

36:44.536 --> 36:46.955
I'm tired. I should go to bed.

36:47.080 --> 36:49.291
[THUNDER RUMBLING]

36:49.416 --> 36:50.375
[SIGHS]

36:50.500 --> 36:54.337
I can't wait to get back on the road
and get out of this weird place.

36:54.462 --> 36:56.256
[THUNDER CONTINUES RUMBLING]

36:56.381 --> 36:58.258
[RAINING]

36:59.175 --> 37:00.594
[GASPS] Shit.

37:00.719 --> 37:01.936
[THUNDER RUMBLING]

37:09.686 --> 37:11.771
It's flashing outside.

37:11.896 --> 37:14.024
You just missed it.

37:14.190 --> 37:16.776
[THUNDER RUMBLING]

37:16.901 --> 37:18.323
[FAUCET RUNNING]

37:24.284 --> 37:26.286
Good night, Jack.

37:27.036 --> 37:28.709
Good night.

37:32.876 --> 37:35.004
[THUNDER CONTINUES RUMBLING]

37:37.464 --> 37:39.057
- Are you all right?
- I'm fine.

37:39.215 --> 37:40.675
Come here.

37:40.800 --> 37:43.019
I'll be all right, really.

37:50.852 --> 37:53.856
- Thanks.
- It's the least I could do.

37:55.398 --> 37:57.241
I'm sorry.

37:58.818 --> 38:00.362
For what?

38:00.487 --> 38:02.447
Everything.

38:02.572 --> 38:04.783
Dinner.

38:04.908 --> 38:07.411
Don't be. It's not your fault.

38:16.169 --> 38:17.421
Thank you.

38:20.757 --> 38:21.724
[SIGHS]

38:24.344 --> 38:26.517
What happened to you, Jack?

38:29.140 --> 38:31.393
It's complicated.

38:33.269 --> 38:35.067
Yeah.

38:37.273 --> 38:39.526
It always is.

38:45.865 --> 38:48.576
I like your tattoo, by the way.

38:48.701 --> 38:50.123
Oh.

38:52.997 --> 38:56.126
From when I was young and free.

38:56.292 --> 38:58.294
Like a butterfly.

39:00.004 --> 39:01.715
Somehow, it seemed personal to me.

39:01.840 --> 39:05.468
Like, a butterfly reminded me...

39:05.593 --> 39:06.970
of myself.

39:07.595 --> 39:09.639
What can I say?

39:09.764 --> 39:11.357
I was young.

39:12.100 --> 39:14.561
You're still young.

39:14.686 --> 39:16.563
And what's age anyway?

39:22.610 --> 39:25.488
Help yourself to anything
in the kitchen, Jack.

39:25.613 --> 39:27.832
Make yourself at home.

39:33.955 --> 39:35.623
GRIZARD: What are you playing at?

39:35.748 --> 39:37.375
What is all this melodrama?

39:37.500 --> 39:38.668
Everything was going well.

39:38.793 --> 39:41.512
You're going to ruin everything.

39:42.255 --> 39:44.382
MARY: Why are you doing this?

39:44.507 --> 39:45.929
I can't do this anymore!

39:46.467 --> 39:47.810
GRIZARD: Did you take your pills?

39:48.011 --> 39:50.847
MARY: No. No! Fuck the medicines!

39:50.972 --> 39:52.015
Fuck them!

39:52.140 --> 39:54.609
[THUNDER RUMBLING]

39:57.896 --> 39:59.864
[FOOTSTEPS]

40:05.361 --> 40:07.572
TV: The company that charters ferries
across the Channel

40:07.697 --> 40:11.659
announces a day of strike and blockades.

40:11.784 --> 40:14.496
Unions did not find an agreement

40:14.621 --> 40:17.624
with the leadership
regarding a salary increase.

40:17.749 --> 40:20.593
- It will be the third day of strike...
- I didn't mean to disturb you.

40:20.835 --> 40:23.046
You're not disturbing me at all.

40:23.171 --> 40:24.263
Come in.

40:24.422 --> 40:26.766
I'm happy to see you.

40:27.759 --> 40:30.386
Passengers have been stuck
for several days...

40:30.511 --> 40:33.973
I'm sitting here in the dark,

40:34.098 --> 40:36.817
alone, by myself.

40:38.436 --> 40:41.815
I'm afraid you can no longer go home.

40:41.940 --> 40:43.608
I'm sorry?

40:43.733 --> 40:46.861
Tomorrow, you'll have to stay.

40:46.986 --> 40:49.531
- What do you mean?
- The strike.

40:49.656 --> 40:50.698
Oh, right.

40:50.823 --> 40:54.248
By the look of things,
the ferries will run again

40:54.410 --> 40:58.790
in two or three days, maybe, at the best.

40:58.915 --> 41:00.333
Oh.

41:00.458 --> 41:04.712
But as I said, you stay here
and make yourself comfortable.

41:04.837 --> 41:06.422
I'm not sure.

41:06.547 --> 41:08.925
I need to speak to Véronique.

41:09.717 --> 41:12.266
We'll see more in the morning.

41:12.971 --> 41:15.690
We say, "Tomorrow is another day."

41:17.266 --> 41:20.019
No need to worry.

41:22.522 --> 41:24.195
What are you doing?

41:25.066 --> 41:27.114
I am looking for...

41:27.986 --> 41:31.030
Let's see, a piece of cloth...

41:31.155 --> 41:32.198
of this size.

41:32.323 --> 41:34.868
Yeah, right.
I saw you looking at his passport.

41:34.993 --> 41:36.961
Oh.

41:39.288 --> 41:40.881
Well...

41:41.874 --> 41:44.043
That's hardly a crime, is it?

41:44.168 --> 41:48.464
Anyway, he put it on the desk.
It was just there.

41:48.589 --> 41:50.307
I can't believe this.

41:50.466 --> 41:53.515
You're not ashamed
of going through other people's stuff?

41:58.474 --> 42:01.728
I'm sorry. You'll have to excuse me.

42:03.146 --> 42:05.148
I'm a bit of a night owl, you know.

42:06.899 --> 42:09.778
Anyway, I think it's time to go to sleep now.

42:15.491 --> 42:17.118
[FLIPPING PAGES]

42:21.122 --> 42:22.544
[SIGHS]

42:30.131 --> 42:32.179
[WIND HOWLING]

42:35.553 --> 42:38.640
TV: Now, following
an unexpected turn of events,

42:38.765 --> 42:39.933
the police seem to think...

42:40.058 --> 42:42.560
Beautiful house. Must get a bit lonely.

42:42.685 --> 42:46.105
Just you two with all this space.

42:46.230 --> 42:49.984
I like quietude. It's good for peace of mind.

42:50.109 --> 42:52.111
What about your children?

42:53.404 --> 42:55.156
Like a taste?

42:55.281 --> 42:58.159
Ah! Just for my sake.

42:58.284 --> 43:00.378
Just to taste it.

43:01.120 --> 43:02.997
The police are concerned there may be

43:03.122 --> 43:05.458
a dozen other victims
whose corpses haven't been found,

43:05.583 --> 43:08.920
and they are investigating cases
of missing persons in the area.

43:09.045 --> 43:11.343
[COUGHS]

43:13.841 --> 43:15.889
We don't have children.

43:16.677 --> 43:17.804
Such is life.

43:17.929 --> 43:22.025
Some things you have, some things not.

43:23.017 --> 43:24.894
I am happy to have a drink with you

43:25.019 --> 43:28.022
because my wife, she doesn't like to drink.

43:28.147 --> 43:31.067
The police advise people
not to pick up hitchhikers...

43:31.192 --> 43:33.152
More than enough, thank you.

43:33.277 --> 43:35.154
Meanwhile, temperatures
are reaching a new high.

43:35.279 --> 43:40.456
She claims it distracts her,
and she can't focus on her painting.

43:42.411 --> 43:44.038
But then she drinks wine.

43:44.163 --> 43:45.961
[CHUCKLING]

43:47.250 --> 43:50.753
My wife's artwork is all over the house.

43:50.878 --> 43:54.215
Oh, I didn't even realize she was an artist.

43:54.340 --> 43:56.308
She is very talented.

43:56.801 --> 43:57.802
And you?

43:57.927 --> 44:01.477
[CLOCK TICKING]

44:04.642 --> 44:06.861
I am a composer.

44:09.230 --> 44:10.277
[CHUCKLES]

44:15.945 --> 44:17.989
I travel a lot, you see. So, it depends.

44:18.114 --> 44:20.908
I am not always a composer. Sometimes.

44:21.033 --> 44:23.661
[HITS KEY ON PIANO]

44:26.372 --> 44:28.499
It's a happy coincidence.

44:28.624 --> 44:30.960
You two being artists.

44:31.085 --> 44:34.214
What kind of music do you compose?

44:34.380 --> 44:36.799
I don't believe in coincidence.

44:36.924 --> 44:41.395
Just destiny, or inevitability.

44:42.305 --> 44:44.023
Right.

44:47.518 --> 44:49.312
And you?

44:49.437 --> 44:52.907
- Me?
- Sure. What do you do?

44:53.733 --> 44:55.861
I'm not really sure yet.

44:56.527 --> 44:59.864
I was thinking of studying archaeology.

44:59.989 --> 45:03.539
I'm fascinated by what societies
from the past have left behind.

45:03.743 --> 45:05.453
Hmm.

45:05.578 --> 45:08.081
But you know, that's really dangerous.

45:08.206 --> 45:10.541
I knew you were one of those.

45:10.666 --> 45:12.627
Prying, snooping around.

45:12.752 --> 45:15.972
But, you know,
some things should be left alone.

45:17.173 --> 45:20.393
Some things are asleep
and should stay that way.

45:21.928 --> 45:23.763
Well, I don't mean to be rude, but...

45:23.888 --> 45:25.890
I don't really understand what you're saying.

45:26.015 --> 45:27.767
I should probably go and get some sleep.

45:27.892 --> 45:30.978
Right. That's understandable.
You've walked a lot.

45:31.103 --> 45:33.481
And all this chatting is tiring, right?

45:33.606 --> 45:35.859
[WIND HOWLING]

45:37.735 --> 45:40.029
We'll talk more about it tomorrow.
Good night.

45:40.154 --> 45:41.781
- Good night.
- Hmm.

45:41.906 --> 45:43.749
[DOOR CLOSING]

45:46.827 --> 45:48.374
[SIGHS]

45:50.915 --> 45:52.758
Keep your door...

45:53.876 --> 45:55.594
locked.

46:02.343 --> 46:04.061
[CRICKETS CHIRPING]

46:12.645 --> 46:14.021
[FLOORS CREAKING]

46:14.146 --> 46:16.274
[METAL CLANGING]

46:49.807 --> 46:51.400
[HEAVY BREATHING]

48:00.961 --> 48:02.554
[STRIKES MATCH]

48:34.912 --> 48:36.004
[FLY BUZZING]

48:58.686 --> 49:00.984
[CAR DOOR OPENING]

49:24.336 --> 49:26.464
[CAR APPROACHING]

49:38.100 --> 49:40.144
[CAR BRAKING]

49:40.269 --> 49:42.192
[CHUCKLING]

49:42.480 --> 49:44.403
[SCREAMING]

49:57.786 --> 49:59.914
[SCREAMING CONTINUES]

50:07.713 --> 50:09.340
[SCREAMING CONTINUES]

50:14.762 --> 50:16.685
[BIRDS CHIRPING]

50:21.894 --> 50:24.773
[WATER SPLASHING]

50:44.708 --> 50:46.381
Hello!

51:02.935 --> 51:04.562
[CHUCKLES]

51:05.604 --> 51:07.447
Oh, wow.

51:20.578 --> 51:23.414
You're a vegetarian, Jack?

51:23.539 --> 51:24.540
Oui?

51:24.707 --> 51:26.550
Ah, shit!

51:29.587 --> 51:31.009
[SIGHS]

51:54.278 --> 51:55.746
Hmm.

51:58.407 --> 52:00.159
[CHUCKLING]

52:07.541 --> 52:08.337
[KNOCKING]

52:08.500 --> 52:10.047
Véronique?

53:14.900 --> 53:16.447
[FUMBLING WITH DOOR]

53:17.361 --> 53:18.954
It's locked.

53:19.738 --> 53:22.241
I was just looking for Véronique.

53:22.366 --> 53:24.994
Oh. She left.

53:25.160 --> 53:26.328
What?

53:26.453 --> 53:28.497
I said your friend is gone.

53:28.622 --> 53:30.958
- What do you mean, she's gone?
- She left.

53:31.083 --> 53:34.295
She said to tell you good-bye and good luck.

53:34.420 --> 53:36.505
No. I don't understand.

53:36.630 --> 53:38.966
There's nothing to understand. She left.

53:39.091 --> 53:41.135
And you should also leave now.

53:41.260 --> 53:44.221
You said you'd give me a lift to Calais.

53:44.346 --> 53:46.390
I'm afraid I won't.

53:46.515 --> 53:49.439
I'm changing my plans.

53:50.436 --> 53:53.531
- Have you a phone I could use?
- No phone.

53:57.776 --> 53:58.902
What's that you've got there?

54:00.738 --> 54:02.740
What? Oh, this?

54:02.865 --> 54:03.991
Oh...

54:05.492 --> 54:07.369
I'm just fixing things.

54:08.871 --> 54:11.373
As you can see, this house is old.

54:11.498 --> 54:14.877
There's always something that breaks,
and I have to fix it.

54:15.002 --> 54:17.221
Where is she? What have you done?

54:17.921 --> 54:21.383
What are you talking about?

54:21.508 --> 54:22.805
Hmm?

54:24.094 --> 54:27.222
What are you worrying about?

54:27.347 --> 54:29.520
No point.

54:30.851 --> 54:34.526
- Relax, Jack.
- Véronique?

54:35.272 --> 54:38.025
- Why? Véronique, Véronique...
- Véronique!

54:38.150 --> 54:40.194
I told you. She left... Véronique.

54:40.319 --> 54:42.697
- Véronique!
- Calm down.

54:43.655 --> 54:45.532
Véronique!

54:46.033 --> 54:48.582
Véronique? Véronique!

54:50.078 --> 54:53.958
- Jack, what are you afraid of?
- Véronique!

54:54.833 --> 54:57.503
Look, she left a note for you.

54:57.628 --> 54:59.426
Read it!

55:20.275 --> 55:21.902
Hmm.

55:22.986 --> 55:25.906
Poor Jack, love is fickle.

55:26.031 --> 55:29.076
But you're young, you'll get over it.

55:29.201 --> 55:30.703
It's just...

55:30.828 --> 55:33.172
Probably for the best.

55:34.081 --> 55:36.792
[BIRDS CHIRPING]

55:36.917 --> 55:38.460
Where's Mary?

55:38.585 --> 55:39.878
Madame Grizard.

55:40.003 --> 55:42.131
She's not here.

55:43.590 --> 55:45.809
You must leave now.

55:47.302 --> 55:50.021
[INSECTS BUZZING]

56:16.790 --> 56:18.838
[HEART BEATS]

56:27.551 --> 56:29.724
[GROANING]

56:31.972 --> 56:33.394
[CONTINUED GROANING]

56:39.271 --> 56:40.693
[ENGINE STOPS]

56:41.732 --> 56:43.200
[SIGHS]

56:44.985 --> 56:46.737
[SIGHS]

56:47.821 --> 56:50.449
Are you awake?
I put you in the back with the animals

56:50.574 --> 56:52.939
because there was no room in the front.

56:53.076 --> 56:54.912
You've reached your final destination,
my poor man.

56:55.037 --> 56:56.914
[PULLS DOWN TAILGATE]

56:58.290 --> 56:59.963
[SIGHS]

57:06.757 --> 57:08.467
[SIGHS]

57:08.592 --> 57:09.718
Here...

57:09.843 --> 57:11.553
I made you some food.

57:11.678 --> 57:13.100
What the fuck?

57:14.097 --> 57:15.269
I hope you like rabbit.

57:15.432 --> 57:17.400
[WHIMPERING] I want to leave.

57:18.977 --> 57:21.146
What? What is it?

57:21.271 --> 57:24.149
Ah, sorry!

57:24.274 --> 57:25.241
Ah!

57:25.442 --> 57:26.819
[GASPING]

57:27.027 --> 57:28.950
What the fuck?

57:30.322 --> 57:33.492
Don't get all worked up, man.
I don't speak English.

57:33.617 --> 57:36.078
I am sorry.

57:36.203 --> 57:37.876
[SIGHS]

57:38.956 --> 57:41.667
Here. You see, this one,

57:41.792 --> 57:43.585
I am keeping for later.

57:43.710 --> 57:45.508
Beautiful animal, right?

57:47.172 --> 57:48.264
[WHIMPERING]

57:48.423 --> 57:49.508
Yes.

57:49.633 --> 57:52.477
Yes. I've been doing this for 10 years.

57:53.011 --> 57:57.224
The State pays me to do the dirty work
nobody else wants to do.

57:57.349 --> 57:59.226
Pick up road kill.

57:59.434 --> 58:01.478
They don't understand, you see.

58:01.603 --> 58:02.563
[CHUCKLING]

58:02.688 --> 58:05.107
It's the best job in the world.

58:05.232 --> 58:08.026
Yes, it is. I am being paid to eat.

58:08.151 --> 58:10.696
But I can't eat it all. Right, Jeanne?

58:10.821 --> 58:11.905
[BARKING]

58:12.030 --> 58:13.949
Sometimes, the poor things
are in such bad shape

58:14.074 --> 58:15.617
that I can't do anything with them.

58:15.742 --> 58:16.994
So, I bury them.

58:17.703 --> 58:20.163
And then, sometimes,

58:20.288 --> 58:24.300
I stuff them, when they're not too damaged.

58:24.459 --> 58:26.545
You see? Like this one.

58:26.670 --> 58:28.593
Or this one.

58:29.965 --> 58:31.137
It's pretty, isn't it?

58:31.758 --> 58:33.260
- [DOG PANTING]
- You know...

58:33.844 --> 58:36.930
Some people are ready to pay
the big bucks to have stuffed animals.

58:37.055 --> 58:38.272
[BARKING]

58:38.640 --> 58:40.688
Yes, yes.

58:43.645 --> 58:45.188
Here you go.

58:45.313 --> 58:47.900
Please, I don't understand.

58:48.025 --> 58:50.494
I don't understand. Please!

58:51.194 --> 58:52.867
Anyhow.

58:54.573 --> 58:57.576
I found you on the road, unconscious,

58:57.701 --> 58:59.578
lying on the ground like those dead animals.

59:00.328 --> 59:02.422
I didn't see that coming.

59:04.041 --> 59:05.500
Although, it's a nice change.

59:05.625 --> 59:07.669
What are you going to do to me?

59:07.794 --> 59:09.341
Yum, yum.

59:09.504 --> 59:11.256
[CRYING]

59:12.424 --> 59:14.468
Eat. It's really good.

59:14.593 --> 59:16.641
There you go.

59:20.599 --> 59:22.809
Come on.

59:22.934 --> 59:25.479
- No, fuck off.
- Oh, yes, yes.

59:25.604 --> 59:28.231
Come on, eat.

59:28.356 --> 59:30.029
[WHIMPERING]

59:31.109 --> 59:34.704
Well, shit. I invite you over for dinner,
and this is how you thank me?

59:41.369 --> 59:42.663
Oh, fuck!

59:42.788 --> 59:44.756
Wait, please... Please!

59:46.458 --> 59:49.382
Stop! No! Why are you doing this?

59:49.544 --> 59:51.387
And why not? Huh?

59:52.255 --> 59:55.300
Wait, don't move.
Or I could cut your little toe.

59:55.425 --> 59:57.970
Please. Please, don't do this. Please!

59:58.095 --> 01:00:02.566
"Please don't do this."
"Please don't do this."

01:00:03.308 --> 01:00:05.268
Stop, stop! No!

01:00:05.393 --> 01:00:06.979
[CHUCKLING]

01:00:07.104 --> 01:00:09.402
What a fool you are.

01:00:09.564 --> 01:00:11.858
I am not going to cut your little toe.

01:00:11.983 --> 01:00:13.819
That would be pure cruelty.

01:00:13.944 --> 01:00:17.030
"What did I do to deserve this?"

01:00:17.155 --> 01:00:18.865
Is that what you were thinking?

01:00:18.990 --> 01:00:20.117
[PANTING]

01:00:20.242 --> 01:00:22.461
[GROWLING]

01:00:23.328 --> 01:00:25.922
There you are. It will do you good.

01:00:28.625 --> 01:00:30.423
[SIGHS]

01:00:32.587 --> 01:00:33.922
[GRUNTING]

01:00:34.047 --> 01:00:36.095
[USING SHEARS]

01:00:37.384 --> 01:00:39.182
[SIGHS]

01:00:42.639 --> 01:00:44.061
[SIGHS]

01:00:45.142 --> 01:00:47.310
What, you're not eating?

01:00:47.435 --> 01:00:49.278
No eat? Eat.

01:00:50.313 --> 01:00:52.190
Come on.

01:00:55.485 --> 01:00:56.987
Hey.

01:00:57.112 --> 01:00:58.910
Look at me.

01:01:03.285 --> 01:01:05.245
That's it.

01:01:05.370 --> 01:01:07.589
You're a good boy.

01:01:09.958 --> 01:01:11.293
[CHUCKLING]

01:01:11.418 --> 01:01:12.635
[EXHALING]

01:01:14.796 --> 01:01:17.640
See, I knew you weren't a "homme-lette".

01:01:19.676 --> 01:01:21.929
Here. Let me taste it.

01:01:26.266 --> 01:01:28.143
Damn, it's so good.

01:01:30.353 --> 01:01:32.776
Don't even think about it.

01:01:34.107 --> 01:01:35.279
What do you mean...

01:01:37.694 --> 01:01:39.822
"Homme-lette"?

01:01:41.656 --> 01:01:44.330
No, no, no, no. Wait a second.

01:01:45.493 --> 01:01:46.870
You know Grizard?

01:01:48.079 --> 01:01:49.623
[BIRDS CHIRPING]

01:01:49.748 --> 01:01:51.921
[GROANING]

01:01:58.924 --> 01:02:01.393
[GROANING CONTINUES]

01:02:03.220 --> 01:02:04.847
[GRUNTS]

01:02:06.014 --> 01:02:09.226
[CHUCKLING]
Shit, you should really see your face.

01:02:09.351 --> 01:02:11.478
Poor little boy.

01:02:11.603 --> 01:02:13.897
All right.

01:02:14.022 --> 01:02:16.191
Say, I'll do you a favor.

01:02:16.316 --> 01:02:17.984
I'll take you to the highway.

01:02:18.109 --> 01:02:19.361
It's not that big of a detour,

01:02:19.486 --> 01:02:22.285
and I have to go by the Chabrol farm
to finish the job.

01:02:23.198 --> 01:02:24.415
[SIGHS]

01:02:30.664 --> 01:02:32.917
[PANTING]

01:02:39.422 --> 01:02:42.801
You won't remember anything when you wake up.

01:02:42.926 --> 01:02:44.803
You'll be back where you started.

01:02:44.928 --> 01:02:47.139
On the road. Imagine that.

01:02:47.264 --> 01:02:49.391
You shouldn't have pissed off Grizard, boy.

01:02:49.516 --> 01:02:51.610
But since he didn't kill you,
you must be strong.

01:02:52.602 --> 01:02:54.020
Come here.

01:02:54.145 --> 01:02:55.613
[WHIMPERING]

01:02:56.982 --> 01:02:58.191
Ah.

01:02:58.316 --> 01:03:00.114
[WHIMPERING CONTINUES]

01:03:03.655 --> 01:03:05.240
Shit.

01:03:05.365 --> 01:03:06.241
[BARKING]

01:03:06.366 --> 01:03:08.535
Damn it, the stove!

01:03:08.660 --> 01:03:10.879
[BARKING]

01:03:13.999 --> 01:03:16.252
[PANTING]

01:03:19.546 --> 01:03:21.389
[FLIES BUZZING]

01:03:45.488 --> 01:03:48.082
All right, let's finish this
once and for all.

01:03:51.828 --> 01:03:53.922
Where the hell did I put them?

01:04:05.508 --> 01:04:07.226
[CLEARS THROAT]

01:04:09.387 --> 01:04:11.264
Damn.

01:04:13.391 --> 01:04:15.485
This little punk is really in trouble now.

01:04:19.522 --> 01:04:23.652
In any case, they don't
pay me enough for this shit.

01:04:23.818 --> 01:04:25.153
[ENGINE STARTING]

01:04:25.278 --> 01:04:26.370
[WHISTLES]

01:04:42.212 --> 01:04:45.423
Hello? Hello? Is anyone there? I need help!

01:04:45.548 --> 01:04:47.141
Hello?

01:04:54.724 --> 01:04:57.273
Goddamn it. Where did he go?

01:04:58.937 --> 01:05:01.147
At least we have his picture.

01:05:01.272 --> 01:05:02.489
We really scared him, huh?

01:05:22.335 --> 01:05:24.133
[LEAVES RUSTLING]

01:05:26.423 --> 01:05:28.972
[BIRDS CHIRPING]

01:05:32.470 --> 01:05:34.313
[PANTING]

01:05:42.147 --> 01:05:44.445
[CAR APPROACHING]

01:05:55.326 --> 01:05:56.953
What are you doing?

01:05:57.078 --> 01:05:58.872
MARY: Something must be done.

01:05:58.997 --> 01:06:00.582
Listen to me!

01:06:00.707 --> 01:06:04.002
The only thing we need to do is go
to town in order to get some pills.

01:06:04.127 --> 01:06:05.253
And then what?

01:06:05.378 --> 01:06:08.173
You think everything will suddenly be fixed?

01:06:08.298 --> 01:06:12.427
When are you going to wake up
and be realistic?

01:06:12.552 --> 01:06:16.973
This is a terrible, awful mess!

01:06:17.098 --> 01:06:19.059
There's no way out!

01:06:19.184 --> 01:06:20.777
Not this time.

01:06:20.935 --> 01:06:23.814
We'll never get out of it.

01:06:23.980 --> 01:06:26.574
- [CRYING]
- It wasn't so...

01:06:29.694 --> 01:06:33.406
It will be a hazy memory for Jack
at the most.

01:06:33.531 --> 01:06:37.035
I spoke to Delacroix
less than half an hour ago.

01:06:37.160 --> 01:06:40.246
And everything was under control.

01:06:40.371 --> 01:06:42.590
Ah, shit.

01:06:43.875 --> 01:06:45.710
We can go and check on them on the way.

01:06:45.835 --> 01:06:49.214
No, I don't want to do that.

01:06:54.344 --> 01:06:56.472
[ENGINE STARTING]

01:07:04.521 --> 01:07:06.694
[CAR TAKING OFF]

01:07:18.243 --> 01:07:19.790
[UNLOCKING DOOR]

01:07:36.386 --> 01:07:38.138
[SOMETHING FALLS ON THE FLOOR]

01:08:19.178 --> 01:08:20.225
Véronique?

01:09:11.229 --> 01:09:13.323
[GROANING]

01:09:16.361 --> 01:09:18.658
[GROANING CONTINUES]

01:09:22.742 --> 01:09:24.868
Fuck! What have they done?

01:09:24.993 --> 01:09:28.872
Jack, they said you left! It was a nightmare!

01:09:28.997 --> 01:09:30.966
I'm such a fool.
I should have listened to you.

01:09:31.125 --> 01:09:33.877
- They told me you had left!
- No! They tried to trick me.

01:09:34.002 --> 01:09:36.714
I knew it. I knew you wouldn't leave me.

01:09:36.839 --> 01:09:38.682
You're so sweet.

01:09:39.341 --> 01:09:40.510
Where are those fucking weirdoes?

01:09:40.635 --> 01:09:42.261
They've left. I don't know where to.

01:09:42.386 --> 01:09:44.471
Fuck!

01:09:44.596 --> 01:09:47.020
You need to cut this thing.

01:09:56.734 --> 01:09:58.736
[CUTTING ROPES]

01:09:58.861 --> 01:10:01.205
[PANTING]

01:10:02.031 --> 01:10:03.616
Oh!

01:10:03.741 --> 01:10:06.286
It's going to be all right. I feared you...

01:10:06.411 --> 01:10:09.836
I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

01:10:11.541 --> 01:10:12.500
[SIGHS]

01:10:12.625 --> 01:10:14.252
[CAR APPROACHING]

01:10:14.377 --> 01:10:16.254
Wait.

01:10:17.964 --> 01:10:21.013
They're back. We have to get out of here!

01:10:41.195 --> 01:10:43.698
[PANTING]

01:11:17.023 --> 01:11:19.025
[LOCKING DOOR]

01:11:23.821 --> 01:11:26.324
That girl cannot leave this house.

01:11:49.096 --> 01:11:51.019
Shit!

01:12:05.655 --> 01:12:08.534
[PANTING]

01:12:16.999 --> 01:12:17.795
[GASPS]

01:12:54.829 --> 01:12:56.502
Hurry.

01:12:58.541 --> 01:12:59.584
Move!

01:12:59.709 --> 01:13:01.382
- [ENGINE STARTS]
- Yes.

01:13:11.387 --> 01:13:13.060
[CRYING]

01:13:16.350 --> 01:13:18.899
[ENGINE STARTS]

01:13:22.481 --> 01:13:23.653
[SCREAMING]

01:13:35.953 --> 01:13:37.497
What the fuck are we going to do?

01:13:37.622 --> 01:13:39.957
Drive. Just keep driving.

01:13:40.082 --> 01:13:42.293
- We need to call the police.
- Jack, there's no time.

01:13:42.418 --> 01:13:44.546
We need to go very far, very quickly.

01:13:49.550 --> 01:13:51.848
Shit! I am losing it.

01:13:55.556 --> 01:13:57.975
- This is all my fucking fault!
- Jack, please don't say that.

01:13:58.100 --> 01:13:59.060
It's not your fault.

01:13:59.185 --> 01:14:01.437
I should've listened to you
from the beginning.

01:14:01.562 --> 01:14:04.690
How am I so naive?
I thought they were nice people.

01:14:04.815 --> 01:14:06.408
I'm always so fucking wrong!

01:14:10.071 --> 01:14:10.780
[CAR GETS RAMMED]

01:14:10.905 --> 01:14:11.997
Fuck!

01:14:16.994 --> 01:14:19.747
He's trying to run us off the road.
Can't believe it!

01:14:24.669 --> 01:14:26.262
Be careful, for God's sake!

01:14:26.420 --> 01:14:29.423
Leave me alone. I know what I am doing.

01:14:29.548 --> 01:14:30.595
Leave it to me.

01:14:31.300 --> 01:14:33.268
This is nuts!

01:14:36.722 --> 01:14:40.067
Come on! This bloody engine!

01:14:42.853 --> 01:14:45.026
- Jesus!
- What the fuck are they doing?

01:14:45.982 --> 01:14:47.825
[TIRES SCREECHING]

01:14:56.659 --> 01:14:57.660
Come on.

01:15:10.256 --> 01:15:12.216
What the fuck are you doing, you sick people?

01:15:12.341 --> 01:15:14.014
Are you crazy?

01:15:19.724 --> 01:15:21.267
Fuck, something's wrong!

01:15:21.392 --> 01:15:22.939
- Look out, Jack!
- Oh, shit!

01:15:30.317 --> 01:15:31.739
[GASPS]

01:15:32.570 --> 01:15:33.696
[TIRES SCREECHING]

01:15:35.364 --> 01:15:39.164
Jack, are you all right?
We have to get out of here!

01:15:40.870 --> 01:15:42.292
Hurry.

01:15:42.580 --> 01:15:44.048
[PANTING]

01:15:45.666 --> 01:15:48.419
- Come on.
- What happened?

01:15:48.544 --> 01:15:49.670
Come with me.

01:15:49.795 --> 01:15:52.139
We are cursed.

01:15:53.299 --> 01:15:56.473
Don't ever forget how much I love you,
no matter what happens.

01:16:05.978 --> 01:16:08.527
They won't go very far on foot.

01:16:55.903 --> 01:16:57.701
Running away is pointless.

01:16:59.365 --> 01:17:01.459
What the fuck are you doing? Go away!

01:17:19.593 --> 01:17:21.687
Come on, what are you waiting for?

01:17:23.681 --> 01:17:25.016
[GUNSHOT]

01:17:25.141 --> 01:17:26.142
God!

01:17:35.651 --> 01:17:37.449
I knew this would happen.

01:17:37.611 --> 01:17:39.196
I knew it, didn't I?

01:17:39.321 --> 01:17:42.033
It's out of control!
What are we supposed to do?

01:17:42.158 --> 01:17:43.576
Calm down, my love. Calm down.

01:17:43.701 --> 01:17:46.625
I am calm! Don't tell me to be calm!

01:17:50.332 --> 01:17:52.835
[PANTING]

01:17:57.631 --> 01:18:00.180
[CONTINUED PANTING]

01:18:09.852 --> 01:18:10.936
[GROANS]

01:18:11.061 --> 01:18:13.147
You English people
aren't so strong after all.

01:18:13.272 --> 01:18:14.648
Just unlucky.

01:18:14.773 --> 01:18:17.026
What's with you
and all the bad luck, seriously?

01:18:17.151 --> 01:18:19.074
Ah, I don't know.

01:18:20.696 --> 01:18:22.448
It can't be all that bad, though.

01:18:22.573 --> 01:18:24.158
I met you, didn't I?

01:18:24.283 --> 01:18:25.951
[CHUCKLING]

01:18:26.076 --> 01:18:28.537
Ah. Oh.

01:18:28.662 --> 01:18:30.039
Oh, God.

01:18:30.956 --> 01:18:32.583
Are you okay?

01:18:32.708 --> 01:18:34.506
Everything's going to be okay.

01:18:34.668 --> 01:18:36.837
[DOOR SCREECHING OPEN]

01:18:36.962 --> 01:18:41.388
Is anyone in here?

01:18:42.468 --> 01:18:43.469
Who is there?

01:18:46.388 --> 01:18:49.107
I've had enough of your nonsense.

01:18:51.185 --> 01:18:53.233
Get out of there.

01:18:54.188 --> 01:18:57.283
I have a knife that cuts,
and I know how to use it.

01:18:58.776 --> 01:19:01.245
Stay here. Don't worry.

01:19:05.282 --> 01:19:07.080
What are you doing here?

01:19:08.285 --> 01:19:09.707
I knew I heard someone.

01:19:10.496 --> 01:19:11.839
- [GUN CLICKS]
- Huh?

01:19:13.499 --> 01:19:15.843
- Are you crazy?
- Fuck.

01:19:18.921 --> 01:19:20.138
I can't believe you did that.

01:19:21.340 --> 01:19:23.134
Leave us alone!

01:19:23.259 --> 01:19:25.845
[TURNS ON SAW]

01:19:25.970 --> 01:19:27.847
Stop playing with that thing.

01:19:27.972 --> 01:19:31.021
It's dangerous. Come on, put it down.

01:19:34.144 --> 01:19:35.566
[SAW SHUTS OFF]

01:19:37.898 --> 01:19:38.899
Leave us alone!

01:19:40.901 --> 01:19:43.028
Come on, little girl.
Calm down. That's enough.

01:19:43.153 --> 01:19:44.450
Leave us alone!

01:19:46.323 --> 01:19:47.366
Come here.

01:19:47.491 --> 01:19:48.993
Oh!

01:19:49.118 --> 01:19:50.461
[COUGHING]

01:19:54.957 --> 01:19:57.255
- Hey.
- Don't you fucking touch her.

01:19:57.835 --> 01:20:00.462
No, no, no. Wait, wait. Stop it.

01:20:00.587 --> 01:20:02.089
Don't do anything stupid.

01:20:02.214 --> 01:20:03.340
[SCREAMING]

01:20:03.465 --> 01:20:04.637
[GROANING]

01:20:12.016 --> 01:20:13.609
Help me, please.

01:20:13.767 --> 01:20:16.812
Ow!

01:20:16.937 --> 01:20:18.522
Help me.

01:20:18.647 --> 01:20:21.025
[WHIMPERING]

01:20:22.026 --> 01:20:24.278
Fuck. Shit.

01:20:24.403 --> 01:20:26.497
[DELACROIX GROANING]

01:20:27.573 --> 01:20:29.158
[SIGHS]

01:20:29.283 --> 01:20:30.242
[CHUCKLING]

01:20:30.367 --> 01:20:31.334
[GROANING]

01:20:33.829 --> 01:20:37.458
Fuck, my head really hurts.

01:20:37.583 --> 01:20:39.301
[GROANING]

01:20:40.252 --> 01:20:42.129
Jack? Jack!

01:20:42.254 --> 01:20:43.756
[COUGHING]

01:20:43.881 --> 01:20:45.554
[CONTINUED GROANING]

01:20:48.886 --> 01:20:52.311
God. It hurts like hell!

01:20:58.020 --> 01:20:59.693
[PANTING]

01:20:59.855 --> 01:21:02.654
[GROANING]

01:21:04.693 --> 01:21:06.661
Help me.

01:21:06.820 --> 01:21:08.864
Ow!

01:21:08.989 --> 01:21:10.407
Aah!

01:21:10.532 --> 01:21:12.830
[PANTING]

01:21:16.955 --> 01:21:18.628
Help me.

01:21:20.042 --> 01:21:21.840
[GROANING]

01:21:28.467 --> 01:21:30.060
[GROANING]

01:21:33.347 --> 01:21:35.432
[DELACROIX EXHALES DEEPLY]

01:21:35.557 --> 01:21:37.275
[PANTING]

01:21:42.564 --> 01:21:45.283
[PANTING]

01:22:01.250 --> 01:22:02.334
We're talking about flesh.

01:22:02.459 --> 01:22:06.839
Flesh and blood. Do you hear me?

01:22:06.964 --> 01:22:08.674
You're listening, but you won't hear.

01:22:08.799 --> 01:22:11.894
No! You listen to me, but you don't hear me!

01:22:13.595 --> 01:22:15.222
Come out!

01:22:15.722 --> 01:22:20.185
- We know you're in there!
- Shit. Shit.

01:22:20.310 --> 01:22:22.483
Come out! Come out!

01:22:23.272 --> 01:22:24.694
[DOOR SCREECHES OPEN]

01:22:52.050 --> 01:22:54.929
He didn't want to play with me.

01:22:56.096 --> 01:22:58.349
But you want to play with me, Dad, don't you?

01:23:00.225 --> 01:23:02.978
What did you do with the boy?

01:23:26.043 --> 01:23:27.761
[CLOSING TRUNK]

01:23:38.847 --> 01:23:41.558
This is the last time I can do this for you.

01:23:41.683 --> 01:23:43.394
I hope you understand.

01:23:43.519 --> 01:23:45.646
I said it was an accident.

01:23:45.771 --> 01:23:48.440
How many times have I heard you say that?

01:23:48.565 --> 01:23:51.485
Why won't you believe me?
He tripped and fell.

01:23:51.610 --> 01:23:54.113
Yeah, right. And as usual,
Daddy has to clean it up.

01:23:54.238 --> 01:23:56.866
I am Mr. Clean, right?

01:23:57.658 --> 01:23:59.205
I'm sorry, Daddy.

01:24:00.035 --> 01:24:02.579
- Listen to me.
- Get out of the car!

01:24:02.704 --> 01:24:03.872
Jack!

01:24:03.997 --> 01:24:06.500
I said, get the fuck out of the fucking car!

01:24:06.625 --> 01:24:08.335
I thought you said he ran away.

01:24:08.460 --> 01:24:11.384
- I can't believe it.
- Get out of the fucking car!

01:24:12.798 --> 01:24:14.721
Give me the keys!

01:24:16.218 --> 01:24:17.845
Don't fucking move. Don't fucking move.

01:24:18.011 --> 01:24:19.471
You don't know what you're doing!

01:24:19.596 --> 01:24:21.223
Oh, really?

01:24:21.348 --> 01:24:22.599
Shall we see, shall we?

01:24:22.724 --> 01:24:23.850
- Please...
- Shall we fucking see?

01:24:24.017 --> 01:24:28.772
- Please, put the gun down. Let's talk.
- Yes! We can explain everything.

01:24:28.897 --> 01:24:31.775
I know everything. You're trying
to make her one of your mannequins.

01:24:31.900 --> 01:24:34.778
- You sick fucks!
- No, Jack, you have to understand.

01:24:35.028 --> 01:24:37.990
- All of this, I was trying to protect you.
- Stop talking!

01:24:38.115 --> 01:24:41.243
- Yes, Jack, there's something I've been...
- Shut the fuck up!

01:24:41.368 --> 01:24:43.245
Tie them up!

01:24:43.370 --> 01:24:45.038
- Get down!
- No.

01:24:45.163 --> 01:24:47.291
This is going way too far, darling.

01:24:47.416 --> 01:24:49.293
Oh, yeah? Too far?

01:24:49.418 --> 01:24:51.671
Then, you shouldn't have come!

01:24:53.672 --> 01:24:55.674
It's your own fault.

01:24:56.300 --> 01:25:00.476
Sooner or later, they will find out
if you keep doing this.

01:25:01.597 --> 01:25:04.729
- Jack!
- Shut up!

01:25:06.143 --> 01:25:08.521
You won't always get away with it!

01:25:09.855 --> 01:25:11.398
No! Véronique!

01:25:11.523 --> 01:25:13.525
I've been wanting to do this for so long.

01:25:13.650 --> 01:25:15.736
You have no right to do this to us, baby.

01:25:15.861 --> 01:25:19.411
I am not a baby anymore.

01:25:20.574 --> 01:25:23.785
And now, of course, you're interested
in what I do. That's too easy.

01:25:23.910 --> 01:25:26.997
Come here. Don't talk to those lunatics.

01:25:27.122 --> 01:25:29.833
So, what are you going to do now?
Are you going to kill us? Kill me?

01:25:29.958 --> 01:25:31.926
Is that it? You want to kill
your mother and I?

01:25:32.085 --> 01:25:35.931
I am leaving with him.
I can't live like this anymore.

01:25:37.257 --> 01:25:38.425
What's gotten into you?

01:25:38.550 --> 01:25:40.260
Shut up, damn it!

01:25:40.385 --> 01:25:41.511
Shut up.

01:25:44.973 --> 01:25:46.683
Dad, I love you.

01:25:46.808 --> 01:25:49.152
I love you, but I hate you.

01:25:51.521 --> 01:25:53.990
You will never understand.

01:25:55.609 --> 01:25:59.071
- Why? Why?
- Because I can't take it anymore.

01:25:59.196 --> 01:26:01.323
I can't be stuck in this idea anymore.

01:26:01.448 --> 01:26:03.621
I am going crazy with you two!

01:26:04.117 --> 01:26:05.327
You don't help me.

01:26:05.452 --> 01:26:07.204
You can't help me.

01:26:07.329 --> 01:26:08.997
For a long time, I hoped you would stop.

01:26:09.122 --> 01:26:10.624
But I must admit it, you're crazy.

01:26:10.749 --> 01:26:12.717
Shut up. Shut up, okay?

01:26:14.336 --> 01:26:15.379
Yes, you're crazy.

01:26:15.504 --> 01:26:17.882
Shut up! Shut up!

01:26:18.882 --> 01:26:21.180
You will never stop.

01:26:22.719 --> 01:26:25.347
I try to get away, but I always come back.

01:26:25.472 --> 01:26:27.270
This time, it's over. I won't come back.

01:26:27.432 --> 01:26:29.025
You will never stop.

01:26:29.184 --> 01:26:30.811
Never. That's the problem.

01:26:30.936 --> 01:26:32.734
You are a killer.

01:26:40.237 --> 01:26:41.489
Véronique!

01:26:42.739 --> 01:26:43.824
- Listen to me.
- That's enough.

01:26:43.949 --> 01:26:45.041
Don't forget that we are...

01:26:45.200 --> 01:26:46.368
- That's enough.
- Listen to me.

01:26:46.493 --> 01:26:47.869
I know you will do it again.

01:26:47.994 --> 01:26:50.247
You need me. We are your only family.

01:26:50.372 --> 01:26:51.582
Listen to me!

01:26:51.707 --> 01:26:54.084
Don't leave! I don't want you to leave.

01:26:54.209 --> 01:26:57.213
Do you understand?
I will do anything for you.

01:26:58.588 --> 01:27:00.306
[MUFFLED VOICE]

01:27:02.259 --> 01:27:04.808
[THUNDER RUMBLING]

01:27:07.514 --> 01:27:09.016
[SIGHS]

01:27:13.270 --> 01:27:14.938
[SIGHING]

01:27:15.063 --> 01:27:17.407
[SOFTLY RAINING]

01:27:19.985 --> 01:27:21.987
One, two, three.

01:27:22.988 --> 01:27:24.535
Scissors!

01:27:26.199 --> 01:27:27.667
[CHUCKLES]

01:27:39.838 --> 01:27:42.682
[FRENCH POP MUSIC PLAYS]

01:27:51.016 --> 01:27:52.859
[LAUGHS]

01:27:54.436 --> 01:27:56.939
Free, at last!

01:27:57.856 --> 01:28:00.359
I couldn't have done this with anyone else.

01:28:00.484 --> 01:28:02.194
Only you.

01:28:02.319 --> 01:28:04.538
[FRENCH POP MUSIC CONTINUES PLAYING]

01:28:05.530 --> 01:28:07.578
What did you say?

01:28:09.910 --> 01:28:11.912
You brought me back to life.

01:28:12.037 --> 01:28:14.836
"You brought me back to life?"

01:28:16.124 --> 01:28:18.673
I love it when you speak in French.

01:28:20.170 --> 01:28:22.589
"Tu me fais revivre."

01:28:22.714 --> 01:28:25.593
You're so beautiful when you speak in French.

01:28:27.719 --> 01:28:28.929
You have to teach me.

01:28:29.054 --> 01:28:32.849
A little bit every day, okay?

01:28:32.974 --> 01:28:34.521
Okay.

01:28:53.995 --> 01:28:55.622
What was that?

01:28:55.747 --> 01:28:57.124
Nothing.

01:28:57.249 --> 01:28:59.718
Just something I don't need anymore.

01:29:02.504 --> 01:29:05.006
- Calais?
- Just drive.

01:29:05.131 --> 01:29:08.635
- But where are we going?
- Anywhere!

01:29:08.760 --> 01:29:10.345
Anywhere but here.

01:29:10.470 --> 01:29:12.264
Shouldn't we go back to your family?

01:29:12.389 --> 01:29:13.890
No.

01:29:14.015 --> 01:29:16.435
They'll be worried, no?

01:29:16.560 --> 01:29:19.855
No. They never have.

01:29:19.980 --> 01:29:22.816
Anyway, I feel safe here.

01:29:22.941 --> 01:29:24.818
With you.

01:29:40.709 --> 01:29:42.211
[FRENCH POP MUSIC ENDS]

01:34:21.364 --> 01:34:23.913
[BIRDS CHIRPING]

01:34:26.619 --> 01:34:29.964
[GROANING]

01:34:39.716 --> 01:34:41.468
[MUFFLED VOICE]

01:34:43.678 --> 01:34:47.478
[CRYING]

01:34:47.640 --> 01:34:50.814
[SOBBING]

